{"article_id":"rgbsmYl0FA36tMvx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Federal health officials rushed Friday","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"to assure a frightened public","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"that Ebola does not pose a serious threat in the U.S. ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"even as the first","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"- and thus far only -","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"diagnosis on American soil exposed potential flaws in border screening , treatment and disposal of contaminated items .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"As Ebola patient Thomas Eric Duncan ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"who showed symptoms of the often-fatal disease","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"shortly after arriving from Liberia ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"was in serious condition","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"and being treated in isolation at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"relatives in Dallas resisted a quarantine amid reports","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that cleanup specialists were balking at disinfecting their home .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Still , Dr. Thomas Frieden , director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"( CDC ) ,","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"insists","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"he 's confident","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"Ebola can be contained in the U.S. ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"unlike in Africa","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"where it has killed more than 3,300","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"since the current outbreak began late last year .","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"\" I have no doubt","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"we will control this case of Ebola","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"so that it does not spread widely , \"","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Frieden said .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"So far , Duncan 's diagnosis is the only verified one in the U.S.","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"A man","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"who was isolated in a Hawaii hospital","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"after showing symptoms consistent with Ebola","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"has been cleared ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"although on Friday , a spokeswoman for Howard University in Washington said","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"the university 's hospital has admiteed a patient","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"who had been in Nigeria","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"and showed possible symptoms .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Frieden 's assurances came amid calls for better screening of U.S.-bound passengers from Ebola-affected nations and word","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"that Duncan 's initial triage was bungled at the hospital .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"At a Dallas apartment","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"where Duncan stayed","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"after arriving Sept. 20 ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"family members were legally quarantined Thursday","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"after refusing to comply with Dallas health officials requests","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"that they stay home .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Doctors are taking the temperatures of four family members in the unit","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"where Duncan was staying","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"twice a day","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"to monitor symptoms","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"as part of the health surveillance efforts","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"being led by CDC officials and local Dallas authorities .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Texas health officials told reporters during a press conference Thursday","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"that the family would be quarantined in their apartment unit for the next 20 days","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"until the potential incubation period for Ebola is over .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"On Thursday , a Springfield , Mo. , microbiologist and emergency trauma physician","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"who runs a charity in Guatemala ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"appeared at Atlanta ' s Hartsfield-Jackson International Airport","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"dressed in protective gear","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"to protest what he called mismanagement of the crisis by the federal Centers for Disease Control and Prevention .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"\" If they ' re not lying ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"they are grossly incompetent , \"","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"said Dr. Gil Mobley ,","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"who cleared airport security","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"wearing a mask , goggles , gloves , boots and a hooded white jumpsuit","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"emblazoned on the back with the words , \" CDC is lying ! \"","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"In Duncan 's homeland , authorities vowed to prosecute him for allegedly lying on an airport screening form","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"by answering \" no \" to questions","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"about whether he had \" cared for an Ebola patient","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"or touched the body of someone","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"who had died in an area","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"affected by Ebola . ''","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"In truth , Duncan reportedly had helped carry a 19-year-old pregnant woman to a taxi","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to go to the hospital","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"just five days before he boarded a U.S.-bound flight .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"The woman later died .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"\" There were no signs of any disease","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"when the gentleman boarded the flight , \"","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"said Dr. Tom Kenyon , director of the CDC ' s Center for Global Health .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"\" This was not a failure of the screening process at the airport . \"","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"But the ease","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"at which Duncan passed the screening ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"coupled with the fact","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"that Ebola victims may not become symptomatic for weeks after exposure ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"raised questions","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"about how best to keep the disease off American soil .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"Jessica Vaughn , a researcher","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"affiliated with the nonprofit Center for Immigration Studies in Washington ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"officials have the right","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"to ban anyone from entering the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"if they pose a potential threat to public health or safety .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"\" Other countries are banning travellers from outbreak countries ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"and we should , too , \"","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Vaughn told The Washington Post .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"\" In the middle of a health crisis , the government should be setting up more robust screening protocols . \"","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"Meanwhile , health officials in Dallas acknowledged","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"that Duncan ' s clothing and bedding were still in plastic bags","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"and had not been removed ,","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"The Dallas Morning News reports .","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"Officials were seemingly unsure how to delegate the removal of contaminated items from the apartment .","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Asked why Duncan 's items and clothing were still at the location ,","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"the county 's Health and Human Services director responded","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that it was n't his agency 's responsibility .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"The items will soon be `` appropriately disposed of , ''","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"a county judge said .","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"Health officials widened their search Thursday to 100 individuals","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"possibly exposed to the disease","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"- tracing contacts of the patient and medical staff","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"who initially treated him .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"Also on Thursday , officials said","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"three more young children potentially had contact with Duncan ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"bringing the number of kids","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"being monitored","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"to eight .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"\" We ' re going to break that risk down to high-risk , no-risk and low-risk ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"and that ' s going to be the basis of our contact tracing , \"","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"said David Daigle , associate director for communications , public health preparedness and response at the CDC .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"Daigle expressed concern about infection control at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"where Duncan is currently in isolation ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"that a team was dispatched","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"to conduct the same kind of contact tracing","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"officials are doing in the local community .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"Zachary Thompson , director of Dallas County Health and Human Services , tried to quell fears in the community of the virus spreading","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"and stressed transparency during the investigation .","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"\" A lot of the individuals","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that we come in contact with","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"will not have any symptoms ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"they will not have any association other than the fact","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"that someone said","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"they were there ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"or they might have had contact , \"","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"Thompson said .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"\" This is local public health surveillance at its best , in what we do day in and day out . \"","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"Police were stationed at the Ivy Apartment complex","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"where the family lives","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"Thursday","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"to keep the peace","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"and assist residents and health officials in the community during the investigation .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"\" We want to make sure","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"we create a calm and safe environment for [ health officials ]","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"to do their work","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"- that ' s our primary focus .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"We have had reverse 911 calls to all the residents ...","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"We ' ve talked to them ,","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"we ' ve explained what happened ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"and we ' ve given them the option","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"to call us back , \"","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"said Dallas city mayor , Mike Rawlings .","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"\" If citizens have any questions ,","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"they need to call 311 .","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"We will be able to give them a full explanation of what ' s happening","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"and answer any questions","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"that are challenging . \"","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"Additional nurses and health professionals were called into schools","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"where the five students","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"that were potentially exposed to Ebola attended .","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"\" Our nurses are making two rounds every school day to every classroom","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"just to check","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"to see","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"if anyone has questions","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"or if there are any symptoms , \"","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"said Mike Miles , superintendent of Dallas Independent School District ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"that additional custodial staff was on hand","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"to clean and disinfect the buildings","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"the students attended .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"Miles stressed the fact","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"that the potential for contamination in the schools was minimal ,","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"but said","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"they were doing extra cleaning","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"to take the possibility off the table .","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"The eight students in the potential contacts were enrolled in a homebound program","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"where they will receive curricular and technology support","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"to complete their coursework","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"while they are out of school .","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"Attendance at the five schools","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"involved in the investigation","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"was down 10 percent Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"but Miles said","depth":8},{"id":177,"text":"he expects it to go back up .","depth":8},{"id":178,"text":"Sally Nuran , manager of the Ivy Apartments","depth":6},{"id":179,"text":"where Duncan was visiting family ,","depth":6},{"id":180,"text":"said during a press conference Thursday","depth":5},{"id":181,"text":"that health officials alerted her of the Ebola case on her property late Monday night .","depth":4},{"id":182,"text":"She confirmed","depth":6},{"id":183,"text":"that the lease for that particular unit lists one adult and two children ,","depth":6},{"id":184,"text":"but said","depth":6},{"id":185,"text":"she does not know","depth":7},{"id":186,"text":"how many people are currently occupying the space .","depth":7},{"id":187,"text":"As part of the monitoring process , the CDC has quarantined the family inside the unit , with strict instructions","depth":7},{"id":188,"text":"not to leave the apartment","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"or even step out on the porch ,","depth":8},{"id":190,"text":"according to Nuran .","depth":6},{"id":191,"text":"The family was set to move out of the apartment","depth":6},{"id":192,"text":"when their lease expired on September 30 .","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"The complex is home to residents of many different nationalities","depth":6},{"id":194,"text":"and translators have been on hand","depth":7},{"id":195,"text":"to distribute information in at least eight different languages ,","depth":7},{"id":196,"text":"according to Nuran ,","depth":6},{"id":197,"text":"who said","depth":7},{"id":198,"text":"she ' s working with the CDC and other government agencies","depth":8},{"id":199,"text":"to educate residents about the current situation .","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"Fliers were placed on residents ' doors in the apartment complex Wednesday night","depth":6},{"id":201,"text":"and more translated fliers will be handed out during a community meeting Thursday ,","depth":6},{"id":202,"text":"according to Nuran ,","depth":6},{"id":203,"text":"who said","depth":7},{"id":204,"text":"language barriers have made it difficult to disseminate information .","depth":7},{"id":205,"text":"All common areas have been disinfected by the CDC ,","depth":4},{"id":206,"text":"she said .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":413,"left":384,"right":412,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":384,"left":298,"right":383,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":268,"right":297,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":257,"right":267,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":257,"left":231,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":212,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":212,"left":0,"right":211,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":208,"right":210,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":210,"left":209,"right":5,"relatio